title: Williamson Murray, military historian who peered beyond battles, dies at 81
description: Dr. Murray studied the intersections of military strategy, politics and industry in World War II and other conflicts.

title: What is happening in Niger, and how could the coup there affect the region?
description: Russia and the Wagner mercenary group have “tried to take advantage” of instability in Niger, Secretary of State Antony Blinken warned Tuesday.

title: ‘Hostile actors’ hacked U.K. voter registry, Electoral Commission says
description: The August 2021 breach, discovered in October 2022, “has no impact” on voters’ “ability to take part in the democratic process,” the government said.

title: Woman told to stop breastfeeding her 5-week-old during international flight
description: Chelsea Williams also said a TUI employee told her that breastfeeding would make people "uncomfortable." Breastfeeding in public is protected under U.K. law.

title: Ireland bids farewell to Sinéad O’Connor, musician and trailblazer
description: Her country found the iconoclastic singer-songwriter at times inconvenient on the issues that most animated her. It's catching up to her, now.

title: 98 arrested in child sex abuse probe launched after FBI agents’ killing
description: The arrests in the United States and Australia came two years after FBI agents Daniel Alfin and Laura Schwartzenberger were killed investigating child sex abuse.

title: What to know about EG.5, the most prevalent covid subvariant in the U.S.
description: Coronavirus subvariant EG.5, nicknamed 'Eris,' is a descendant of Omicron.

title: Is it a meteor? A UFO? No, it’s probably a Russian rocket returning to Earth.
description: Australia’s space agency said the fireball many thought was a meteor was likely remnants of a Russian rocket "planned to safely reenter the atmosphere."

title: Australian aid policy to focus on climate — and countering China
description: With its new approach to aid, Anthony Albanese's government is trying to present Australia as an alternative to China, known for "debt-trap diplomacy."

title: Ukraine live briefing: Russian strikes kill 11, officials say; woman held in alleged plot to assassinate Zelensky
description: Deadly Russian assaults in at least four regions across Ukraine damaged homes and farms, officials said. Children and rescue workers were among many injured.

title: Russians tied to Putin or military sidestep sanctions and draw protest
description: Some politicians and activists are calling for tougher punishment of wealthy Russians who live in Europe and have not faced penalties over the war in Ukraine.

title: Imran Khan’s arrest shows how Pakistan’s military calls the shots
description: It's a well-worn truism about the South Asian nation: Most states have armies, but, in Pakistan, the army has a state.
